epartment of Education now has three assistant\ndeputy ministers when there used to be two, and one was bilingual. ","index":"00234","speaker":"Dougald Lamont"},{"html":"<b>*</b>\n(14:30) ","index":"00235","speaker":""},{"html":"����� The K-to-12 review will abolish school boards, and it turns out\nthis government will handpick principals. It's clear to us that in the last\nyear, teachers, school divisions and students all pulled through despite this\ngovernment, not because of it. ","index":"00236","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Has the Premier ever considered the real problem with our school\nsystem is not the teachers or the school divisions, but the politicians like\nhimself who've been running the system for decades? How much did Treasury Board\nrewrite this report? ","index":"00237","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon.\nBrian </b><b><a name=\"_Toc66774462\">Pallister</a></b><b>�(Premier):</b> As usual, Madam Speaker, the member left the ranch,\nwent for a run around the entire country and came back without a conclusion. ","index":"00238","speaker":"Brian Pallister"},{"html":"����� I can only assume that he wants more adminis�trative costs, not\nfewer. I can only assume that he wants poorer results, not better. ","index":"00239","speaker":""},{"html":"����� We\nwant to move the resources that we spend, in abundance, in education to the\nclassroom where they can help our children. That's our focus. ","index":"00240","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Ms. Cindy\n</b><b><a name=\"_Toc66774464\">Lamoureux</a></b><b>�(Tyndall Park):</b> The provincial government was provided\n$85&nbsp;million from the federal government to reopen our schools safely for\nthe 2020-21 school year and, evidently, the Province decided not to use all of\nthis money. ","index":"00241","speaker":"Cindy Lamoureux"},{"html":"����� The Pallister government claimed that the Remote Learning Support\nCentre would cost $10&nbsp;million, yet�and I am tabling a FIPPA document from\nthis past January proving this�no 