��� Thank you. ","index":"00460","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Ms. Nahanni Fontaine (Official\nOpposition House Leader):</b> Is there leave of the House to revert back to\npetitions for the member�Elmwood? ","index":"00461","speaker":"Nahanni Fontaine"},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> Is there leave from the House to revert back to petitions\nfor the honourable member for Elmwood to present his petition? <i>[Agreed]</i> ","index":"00462","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> The honourable member for Elmwood, on a petition. �","index":"00463","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Jim </b><b><a name=\"_Toc66774496\">Maloway</a></b><b>�(Elmwood):</b> I wish to present\nthe following petition to the Legislative Assembly.","index":"00464","speaker":"Jim Maloway"},{"html":"����� The background of� ","index":"00465","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Deputy Speaker:</b> Could the\nhonourable member for Elmwood, please put his mic on, because we can't hear you\nvery well. ","index":"00466","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nMaloway:</b> We're not getting anywhere here again. ","index":"00467","speaker":"Jim Maloway"},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> Okay. ","index":"00468","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nMaloway:</b> It worked before. Hello. ","index":"00469","speaker":"Jim Maloway"},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> We just have to speak louder, then. ","index":"00470","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nMaloway:</b> Oh. Thank you, Mr. Deputy Speaker� ","index":"00471","speaker":"Jim Maloway"},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> That's better. ","index":"00472","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nMaloway:</b> �so you can't�you can hear me a bit then.","index":"00473","speaker":"Jim Maloway"},{"html":"����� The\nbackground to this petition is as follows:","index":"00474","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (1)\nUntil recently, diagnostic medical tests, including for blood and fluid\nsamples, were available and accessible in most medical clinics. ","index":"00475","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (2)\nDynacare blood test labs have consolidated their blood and fluid testing\nservices by closing 25 of its labs. ","index":"00476","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (3)\nThe provincial government has cut diag�nostic testing at many clinic sites, and\nresidents now have to travel to different locations to get their testing done,\neven for a simple blood test or urine sample. ","index":"00477","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (4)\nFurther, travel challenges for vulnerable and elderly residents of northeast\nWinnipeg may result in fewer tests being done or delays in testing, with the\nattendant effects of increased health-care costs and poorer individual patient\noutcomes. ","index":"00478","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (5)\nCOVID‑19 emergency rules have resulted in long outdoor lineups, putting\nvulnerable residents at further risk in extreme weather, being hot or cold.\nMoreover, these long lineups have resulted in longer wait times for services\nand poorer service in general. ","index":"00479","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (6)\nManitoba residents value the convenience and efficiency of the health-care\nsystem when they are able to give their samples at the time of the doctor\nvisit. ","index":"00480","speaker":""},{"html":"����� We\npetition the Legislative Assembly of Manitoba as follows: ","index":"00481","speaker":""},{"html":"����� To\nurge the provincial government to immedi�ately demand Dynacare maintain all the\nphlebotomy, blood sample sites existing prior to the COVID‑19 health\nemergency, and allow all Manitobans to get their blood and urine tests done\nwhen visiting their doctor, thereby facilitating local access to blood testing\nservices. ","index":"00482","speaker":""},{"html":"����� And\nthis petition is signed by many Manitobans. ","index":"00483","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon.\nKelvin Goertzen (Government House Leader):</b> I'm asking leave of the House,\nafter consultation with the Official Opposition House Leader (Ms. Fontaine) and\nthe member for River Heights (Mr. Gerrard), to bring forward a motion regarding\na Sessional Order.� ","index":"00484","speaker":"Kelvin Goertzen"},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nDeputy Speaker:</b> Is it will of the House to bring the�is there leave from\nthe House�is it leave for the House to interrupt bill amendment�Bill 47, and go\nback to government's motion for Sessional Order? ","index":"00485","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Is\nthere leave? <i>[Agreed]</i> ","index":"00486","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon.\nKelvin </b><b><a name=\"_Toc66774502\">Goertzen</a></b><b>�(Government\nHouse Leader):</b> I thank members of the House.","index":"00487","speaker":"Kelvin Goertzen"},{"html":"����� I\nmove, seconded by the Minister of Agriculture,","index":"00488","speaker":""},{"html":"THAT the\nfollowing Sessional Order applies for the 3rd Session of the 42nd Legislature,\ndespite any other rule or practice of this House.","index":"00489","speaker":""},{"html":"THAT in the\nevent of a discrepancy with the existing rules, the provisions of the Sessional\nOrder are to apply. ","index":"00490","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Deadline\ndates </b>","index":"00491","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>1.�� </b>To be\nconsidered specified, government bills before the House must be distributed to\nall members by 5&nbsp;p.m. on March&nbsp;16, 2021.","index":"00492","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>2.�� </b>The\ndeadlines for specified bills will be moved to the following sitting days:","index":"00493","speaker":""},{"html":"(a)� Second\nreading�March&nbsp;24 and 25, 2021","index":"00494","speaker":""},{"html":"(b)� Official\nopposition designation of five bills�March&nbsp;24, 2021, to be announced at\nthe beginning of orders of the day","index":"00495","speaker":""},{"html":"(c)� Committee\nstage�April&nbsp;27, 2021","index":"00496","speaker":""},{"html":"(d)� Committee\nreports�April&nbsp;28, 2021","index":"00497","speaker":""},{"html":"(e)� Report\nstage�May&nbsp;11, 2021 ","index":"00498","speaker":""},{"html":"(f)� Concurrence and\nthird reading�May&nbsp;20, 2021 ","index":"00499","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>3.</b>�� On\nMarch&nbsp;24 and 25, 2021, if the House has not reached orders of the day by\n3:30&nbsp;p.m., the Speaker will terminate routine proceedings and proceed\ndirectly to orders of the day.","index":"00500","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Debate</b>","index":"00501","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>4.</b>�� On March&nbsp;15, 16, 17, 18 and 23, 2021, during orders of\nthe day, government business, the Government House Leader may only call for\ndebate second readings of bills which may be considered specified.","index":"00502","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>5.</b>�� On March&nbsp;22, 2021, the House will consider Interim\nSupply, with the House to not see the clock until royal assent of the interim\nappropriation act is granted. If royal assent occurs before 5&nbsp;p.m. the\nGovernment House Leader may only call for debate second reading of bills which\nmay be considered specified.","index":"00503","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>6.</b>�� On March&nbsp;24, 2021, starting at the beginning of orders\nof the day, government business, the provisions outlined for limited debate on\nspecified bills in rule&nbsp;2(10) will apply, with the exception that after\neach debate concludes the Speaker shall put the question.","index":"00504","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>7.</b>�� The hour of adjournment on May&nbsp;24, 2021<span lang=\"EN-US\">�seven,<b>\n</b>the hour of adjournment on March 24th, 2021 will be midnight.</span>","index":"00505","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>8.</b>��\nOn March&nbsp;25, 2021, starting at the beginning of orders of the day,\ngovernment business, the provisions outlined for limited debate on specified\nbills in rule&nbsp;2(10) will apply, with the exception that after each debate\nconcludes the Speaker shall put the question. ","index":"00506","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>9.</b>��\nAt midnight on March&nbsp;25, 2021, for any remaining specified bills, the\nministers shall move the second reading motions